eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.engine

Interface IValueFinder<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - Type of the keys used for the identifiers.
    V - Type of the attribute values associated with the identifiers.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CategoricalValueFinder, NumericalValueFinder, SpatialValueFinder

    public interface IValueFinder<K,V>
    Interface for retrieving attribute values for a given object identifier.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Object find(Map<K,V> map, K k)
      Retrieve the attribute value available in the dataset for a given object identifier.

      • find

        Object find(Map<K,V> map,
            K k)
        Retrieve the attribute value available in the dataset for a given object identifier.
        Parameters:
        map - The in-memory dataset to be searched.
        k - The key (identifier) of the object.
